# ==========================================================================
# LLM Operator — OpenRouter Chat Completion
#
# The core chat completion interface exposed via OpenRouter's Python SDK.
# At execution time the resolver instantiates OpenRouter(api_key=…) and
# calls client.chat.send(messages=…, model=…, temperature=…, …).
# Ref: https://github.com/OpenRouterTeam/python-sdk
# ==========================================================================

openrouter.chat.completion is an Operator
openrouter.chat.completion is a LLM Chat Completion
openrouter.chat.completion performs Text Generation
openrouter.chat.completion performs Conversational AI
openrouter.chat.completion performs Code Generation
openrouter.chat.completion performs Summarization
openrouter.chat.completion performs Question Answering
openrouter.chat.completion performs Text Classification with LLM
openrouter.chat.completion performs Structured Extraction
openrouter.chat.completion implements Large Language Model

# ---- Parameters ----
# api_key is the only __init__ param (on the operator itself).
openrouter.chat.completion has parameter api_key; is of type env

# chat.send method params — declared on the method node (reached via
# interface calls chain: LLM Chat Completion calls chat.send).
chat.send has parameter messages; is of type list; with default [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}]
chat.send has parameter model; is of type categorical; with default openai/gpt-4o; with choices openai/gpt-4o,openai/gpt-4o-mini,anthropic/claude-sonnet-4,anthropic/claude-haiku-4,google/gemini-2.0-flash-001,meta-llama/llama-3.1-70b-instruct
chat.send has parameter temperature; is of type float; with default 1.0; with low 0.0; with high 2.0
chat.send has parameter top_p; is of type float; with default 1.0; with low 0.0; with high 1.0
chat.send has parameter max_tokens; is of type int; with default 1024; with low 1; with high 128000
chat.send has parameter frequency_penalty; is of type float; with default 0.0; with low -2.0; with high 2.0
chat.send has parameter presence_penalty; is of type float; with default 0.0; with low -2.0; with high 2.0
# seed is optional (UNSET by default in the SDK) — omitted from DnD params.
# chat.send has parameter seed; is of type int; with low 0; with high 2147483647

# ==========================================================================
# LLM-specific Risk taxonomy
#
# These risks are structurally different from traditional ML risks.
# They cannot be validated with statistical checks on a DataFrame;
# instead they require runtime guardrails operating on text.
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Top-level LLM risk categories ----
Prompt Injection is a Risk
Hallucination is a Risk
Toxicity is a Risk
Data Exfiltration is a Risk
Over-reliance is a Risk
Jailbreaking is a Risk

# ---- LLM Risk → EU AI Ethics Principle mappings ----
Prompt Injection is threat to Technical Robustness
Prompt Injection is threat to Human Agency
Hallucination is threat to Transparency
Hallucination is threat to Accountability
Toxicity is threat to Diversity Non-Discrimination Fairness
Toxicity is threat to Societal Wellbeing
Data Exfiltration is threat to Privacy
Over-reliance is threat to Human Agency
Jailbreaking is threat to Technical Robustness

# ==========================================================================
# Operator → Risk mappings (might_introduce)
# ==========================================================================

openrouter.chat.completion might introduce Prompt Injection
openrouter.chat.completion might introduce Hallucination
openrouter.chat.completion might introduce Toxicity
openrouter.chat.completion might introduce Data Exfiltration
openrouter.chat.completion might introduce Over-reliance
openrouter.chat.completion might introduce Jailbreaking

# ==========================================================================
# LLM Checks — guardrail-oriented
#
# These map to check function stubs in dorian/toolbox/checks.py.
# Unlike statistical checks they operate on text (prompts / responses),
# not on DataFrames, so they are skipped during dataset profiling and
# invoked at pipeline execution time.
# ==========================================================================

prompt_injection_scan is a Check
prompt_injection_scan checks for Prompt Injection

toxicity_scan is a Check
toxicity_scan checks for Toxicity

pii_leak_scan is a Check
pii_leak_scan checks for Data Exfiltration

hallucination_check is a Check
hallucination_check checks for Hallucination

# ==========================================================================
# LLM Mitigations — Guardrails
#
# Guardrails are the LLM analogue of traditional bias mitigations.
# They use the same rewrite annotation system (insert_before,
# insert_after, add_parameter) to transform the pipeline DAG.
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Input Guardrail ----
Input Guardrail is a Mitigation
Input Guardrail with description Validate and sanitize user prompts before the LLM call
Input Guardrail with long description "Insert an input validation node upstream of {operator} that scans user prompts for injection patterns, strips disallowed characters, and enforces length limits. This addresses {risk} by filtering adversarial inputs before they reach the language model."

# ---- Output Guardrail ----
Output Guardrail is a Mitigation
Output Guardrail with description Validate and filter LLM responses after generation
Output Guardrail with long description "Insert an output validation node downstream of {operator} that scans generated text for harmful content, PII, or policy violations. This addresses {risk} by catching problematic outputs before they reach the end user."

# ---- System Prompt Hardening ----
System Prompt Hardening is a Mitigation
System Prompt Hardening with description Add security instructions to the system message
System Prompt Hardening with long description "Add a system_prompt Parameter to {operator} containing explicit boundary instructions (role confinement, refusal directives, output format constraints). This addresses {risk} by reducing the model susceptibility to adversarial manipulation through prompt-level defenses."

# ---- Content Filtering ----
Content Filtering is a Mitigation
Content Filtering with description Detect toxicity and PII in LLM outputs
Content Filtering with long description "Insert a content filtering node downstream of {operator} that runs toxicity classification and PII entity detection on the generated text. Flagged responses are blocked or redacted. This addresses {risk} by preventing harmful or privacy-violating content from reaching users."

# ---- Grounding ----
Grounding is a Mitigation
Grounding with description Fact-check LLM output against a knowledge source
Grounding with long description "Insert a retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) verification node downstream of {operator} that cross-references the generated text against a trusted knowledge base. Claims not supported by the source material are flagged. This addresses {risk} by reducing unsupported or fabricated content."

# ---- Temperature Reduction ----
Temperature Reduction is a Mitigation
Temperature Reduction with description Lower the temperature parameter to reduce randomness
Temperature Reduction with long description "Set the temperature Parameter on {operator} to a low value (0.0-0.3) to make outputs more deterministic and factual. High temperature increases creative but potentially inaccurate generation. This addresses {risk} by constraining the sampling distribution."

# ==========================================================================
# Mitigation → Risk mappings (might_mitigate)
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Injection / Jailbreaking defenses ----
Input Guardrail might mitigate Prompt Injection
Input Guardrail might mitigate Jailbreaking
System Prompt Hardening might mitigate Prompt Injection
System Prompt Hardening might mitigate Jailbreaking
System Prompt Hardening might mitigate Over-reliance

# ---- Output safety ----
Output Guardrail might mitigate Toxicity
Output Guardrail might mitigate Data Exfiltration
Output Guardrail might mitigate Hallucination
Content Filtering might mitigate Toxicity
Content Filtering might mitigate Data Exfiltration

# ---- Factuality ----
Grounding might mitigate Hallucination
Grounding might mitigate Over-reliance
Temperature Reduction might mitigate Hallucination

# ==========================================================================
# Ontological rewrite metadata — interface targeting + parameter signature
#
# Rule bodies (pattern + transformations) live in ``expdb.rewrites``
# collection.  The KB declares which interface each mitigation applies to,
# which IO ports it anchors on, and which parameters it exposes.
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Interface targeting ----
Input Guardrail applies to LLM Chat Completion
Output Guardrail applies to LLM Chat Completion
Content Filtering applies to LLM Chat Completion
Grounding applies to LLM Chat Completion
System Prompt Hardening applies to LLM Chat Completion
Temperature Reduction applies to LLM Chat Completion

# ---- IO anchoring (insert_before intercepted ports) ----
Input Guardrail has input messages

# ---- Parameter signature ----
System Prompt Hardening has parameter system_prompt
Temperature Reduction has parameter temperature
system_prompt is of type str
temperature is of type float
